    <fr:title text="Finite Dimensional Vector Space">Finite Dimensional Vector Space</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>A vector space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> is finite <fr:link href="/forest/0018/" title="Dimension of a Finite Vector Space" uri="https://andrewczezowski.github.io/forest/0018/" display-uri="0018" type="local">dimensional</fr:link> if there exists a list of vectors that <fr:link href="/forest/0016/" title="Span and Spans" uri="https://andrewczezowski.github.io/forest/0016/" display-uri="0016" type="local">spans</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex>. Note that by definition lists are finite.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
